comments: Tatum (BOS) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Sexton (CLE) and Theis (BOS) make marginal contact with one another as they briefly engage and separate in the post.
Garland (CLE) makes marginal contact with Walker's (BOS) arm during his follow through.
Smart (BOS) and Love (CLE) briefly engage and separate off ball in the post.
Theis (BOS) initiates marginal contact with Love (CLE) off ball in the post that does not dislodge him from his legal guarding position.
Theis (BOS) clamps Love's (CLE) arm during the rebound.
Hayward (BOS) briefly brings one hand to Thompson's (CLE) front and he immediately slides it off.
Sexton (CLE) and Walker (BOS) briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
Walker (BOS) brings two hands to the ball and continues his dribble.
Smart (BOS) delivers contact to Sexton's (CLE) body and the contact affects his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Love (CLE) during his shot attempt. The contact to Love's (CLE) back is deemed marginal.
Theis (BOS) and Thompson (CLE) briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
Sexton (CLE) cleanly ties up Walker (BOS), any additional contact is considered incidental.
Smart (BOS) and Love (CLE) briefly engage and separate off ball during the jump ball.
Theis (BOS) initiates marginal contact with Sexton (CLE) during the pick that does not affect his ability to defend.
Sexton (CLE) commits a take foul on Walker (BOS).
Thompson (CLE) extends two hands into Theis' (BOS) back causing him to deliver illegal body contact to Sexton (CLE) during his driving shot attempt.
